OL,3,CHunt admits Treasury's costing of
OL,4,CLabour energy efficiency plans may be
OL,5,Cwrong
OL,7,FPeston challenged the assumptions that
OL,8,FTreasury officials were given by the
OL,9,Fchancellor's aides when making the
OL,10,Fcalculations, in particular that a
OL,11,FLabour government would not means-test
OL,12,Fany grants given to homeowners or
OL,13,Fshare the costs with energy companies.
OL,15,FWhen it was put to the chancellor that
OL,16,Fthe assumptions were unrealistic and
OL,17,Ftherefore the Treasury calculation was
OL,18,Ftoo high, Mr Hunt admitted to ITV News
OL,19,Fthat "even if it's not double the #6
OL,20,Fbillion, it is still a very big chunk
OL,21,Fof a #28 billion spending spree".
