OL,7,FThe Treasury's analysis is also not
OL,8,Fthe first time the opposition has
OL,9,Fclashed with the government over
OL,10,Fpolicy costings.
OL,12,FCatherine Haddon, from the Institute
OL,13,Ffor government think tank, said such
OL,14,Fcostings was a "long-standing
OL,15,Fconvention" but also a "political
OL,16,Ftool".
OL,18,F"Costing opposition policies has
OL,19,Fhappened since at least the 1950s.
OL,20,FIt's very much a political tool.
