OL,7,F"The Treasury only do the calculations
OL,8,Fbased on assumptions about the policy
OL,9,Fwhich have to be given to them by
OL,10,Fministers or special advisers.
OL,12,F"It's a long-standing convention," she
OL,13,Fsaid in a post on X.
OL,15,FFormer Treasury permanent secretary
OL,16,FLord Macpherson suggested in a post on
OL,17,FX that such costings should be ignored.
